05/12/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- A committee headed by Joska Broz, the grandson of former Yugoslavia leader Josip Broz Tito, has managed to collect 12,000 signatures necessary to set up a communist party, local media reported on Friday (December 3rd). 
The list will be submitted for registration on Monday. 
All other legal conditions for establishing the party have been met and all necessary registration documents are in order, the committee announced. 
(Blic, Srbijanet, Index.hr - 03/12/10)
